%description:

Checks that an MLDv2 host reports source-filtered multicast state changes of the
interface. The IPv6/MLD counterpart of IGMPv3_host1.test (RFC 3810 §6.1; mirrors
RFC 3376 §5.1 for IGMPv3).

A scriptable TestMld tester drives a sequence of <set-filter> commands on its single
interface, taking the (interface, group) filter through INCLUDE -> INCLUDE -> EXCLUDE ->
EXCLUDE -> INCLUDE transitions, and dumps the resulting interface filter after each step.
The test asserts:
  1. the merged interface filter after each command (<dump what="groups"/>),
  2. the Mldv2 "Old state / New state" log for each transition, and
  3. that the Mldv2 module immediately emits the correct State-Change Report record:
       INCLUDE() -> INCLUDE(S1,S2)  : ALLOW(S1,S2)
       INCLUDE(S1,S2) -> INCLUDE(S1): BLOCK(S2)
       INCLUDE(S1) -> EXCLUDE(S2)   : TO_EX(S2)
       EXCLUDE(S2) -> EXCLUDE(S1,S2): BLOCK(S1)   [EXCLUDE(A)->EXCLUDE(B): BLOCK(B-A)]
       EXCLUDE(S1,S2) -> INCLUDE(S1): TO_IN(S1)
The reports the Mldv2 module sends are looped back to the tester and decoded by
TestMld::handleMessage as "TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<...>".

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib
sim-time-limit=10s
cmdenv-express-mode = false

#omnetpp 5.0 - 5.1 compatibility:
eventlog-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.elog"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sca"
output-vector-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.vec"
snapshot-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sna"

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TestMLDNetwork
**.mld.typename = "Mldv2"
**.multicastForwarding = false

# RFC 3810 6.1: each State-Change Report is sent [Robustness Variable] (=2) times.
# Pin the RNG seed and shrink the Unsolicited Report Interval so the single
# retransmission of each change fires deterministically (< 1s, before the next step).
seed-set = 0
**.mld.unsolicitedReportInterval = 0.5s

**.scenarioManager.script = xmldoc("scenario.xml")

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

%file: scenario.xml
<scenario>

<dump t="1" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" what="groups"/>

<set-filter t="2" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" group="ff3e::1" sources="I 2001::1 2001::2"/>
<dump t="2" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" what="groups"/>

<set-filter t="3" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" group="ff3e::1" sources="I 2001::1"/>
<dump t="3" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" what="groups"/>

<set-filter t="4" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" group="ff3e::1" sources="E 2001::2"/>
<dump t="4" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" what="groups"/>

<set-filter t="5" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" group="ff3e::1" sources="E 2001::1 2001::2"/>
<dump t="5" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" what="groups"/>

<set-filter t="6" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" group="ff3e::1" sources="I 2001::1"/>
<dump t="6" module="node.tester.mac" ifname="eth0" what="groups"/>

</scenario>

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

%#
%# First check that the set-filter commands modified the interface state
%#
%postrun-command: grep "TestMld: .* groups = " test.out > groups.out || true
%contains: groups.out
TestMld: eth0: groups = ff3e::1 I 2001::1 2001::2.
TestMld: eth0: groups = ff3e::1 I 2001::1.
TestMld: eth0: groups = ff3e::1 E 2001::2.
TestMld: eth0: groups = ff3e::1 E 2001::1 2001::2.
TestMld: eth0: groups = ff3e::1 I 2001::1.

%#
%# Now check the state transitions of the Mldv2 module
%#
%postrun-command: grep -E "State of group|Old state:|New state:" test.out > mld.out || true
%contains: mld.out
State of group 'ff3e::1' on interface 'eth0' has changed:
    Old state: INCLUDE().
    New state: INCLUDE(2001::1,2001::2).
State of group 'ff3e::1' on interface 'eth0' has changed:
    Old state: INCLUDE(2001::1,2001::2).
    New state: INCLUDE(2001::1).
State of group 'ff3e::1' on interface 'eth0' has changed:
    Old state: INCLUDE(2001::1).
    New state: EXCLUDE(2001::2).
State of group 'ff3e::1' on interface 'eth0' has changed:
    Old state: EXCLUDE(2001::2).
    New state: EXCLUDE(2001::1,2001::2).
State of group 'ff3e::1' on interface 'eth0' has changed:
    Old state: EXCLUDE(2001::1,2001::2).
    New state: INCLUDE(2001::1).

%#
%# Now check that the Mldv2 module sent the reports immediately, looped back to the
%# tester. Each State-Change Report is sent twice (RFC 3810 6.1: [Robustness Variable]
%# = 2 transmissions): the immediate report followed by one retransmission within the
%# Unsolicited Report Interval, before the next scenario step.
%#
%postrun-command: grep "TestMld: Received" test.out > received.out || true
%contains: received.out
TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=ALLOW (2001::1,2001::2)>.
TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=ALLOW (2001::1,2001::2)>.
TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=BLOCK (2001::2)>.
TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=BLOCK (2001::2)>.
TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=TO_EX (2001::2)>.
TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=TO_EX (2001::2)>.
TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=BLOCK (2001::1)>.
TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=BLOCK (2001::1)>.
TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=TO_IN (2001::1)>.
TestMld: Received: inet::Mldv2Report<ff3e::1=TO_IN (2001::1)>.

%#
%# Explicitly assert the State-Change Report retransmission (RFC 3810 6.1).
%#
%postrun-command: grep "Retransmitting State-Change Report" test.out > retransmit.out || true
%contains: retransmit.out
Retransmitting State-Change Report for group 'ff3e::1' on interface 'eth0' (1 transmission(s) left).
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
